rComments: Really a good and fantastic professor: attentive, patient and helpful. You only have to attend to succeed this course.
Really cares about students and does everything he can for you to do well.
He was a bit hard to understand due to his accent, however he was a great prof and cares about his students, very nice guy and always helped people with problems.

His lectures were a bit hard to understand, but its not even a big deal. If you learn all the material, you're set if you have this guy. He makes his tests and finals really easy and honestly wants you to do good. Props to this guy and what a goat teacher!
I found the lectures very interesting!
J'ai trouvé le cours très intéressant, très drôle et très motivant !
Explications pas compréhensible, je n'ai pas compris sa manière de noter les exams. Et les notes des exams étaient en retard. Je n'ai pas du tout aimé ce cours à cause de lui.

Ce cours était le plus intéressant que j'avais pris ! puisque différent que tous les autres cours de maths. Je vous conseille de prendre ce cours si vous voulez plonger dans l'histoire depuis l'antiquité. Le Professeur Ammar nous explique les nouveaux (bien vraiment anciens) concepts d'une manière efficace,

His lectures were boring and unclear. He got the notes from another teacher and would just read the slides. You have to attend class because he doesn't record or post the annotated notes. He is very accessible after class. He forgot to mark my first midterm and I had to ask him over and over again for a simple grade. He isn't the worst but avoid.
I liked the professor
He's awesome... Dr. Ammar is very considerate of his students and tried to make the classes interesting.
Good and respectable teacher.
Very good teacher, sometimes it is difficult to be clear during the lesson, but he offers all the tools to understand.
A good teacher, he has a sincere desire to transmit and understand the subject.

Dr. Ammar est très bon professeur. Il maitrise bien son matière. Il reprend à tous les questions à la fin de la séance. Beaucoup des devoirs et des examens nous permettent de bien comprendre la matière.

Dr. Ammar isn't an amazing prof, but I gave him a 3 because the class itself isn't hard, and is structured well. Lectures aren't great, but the textbooks are good, and the weekly homework assignments are time consuming, but you learn a lot. Exams aren't very hard, and in fact are easier than the homework. Just do all the work and it's an easy A.

The material isn't very hard, lectures are ok. Work pays off. The main issue with this professor is his lack of character. Professor has an overall ignorant attitude: does not record lectures for stated attendance reasons. Does not answer emails. No TA for help. Seems to think students are irresponsible while making no attempt to better himself.

His class was difficult from the start. His lectures were difficult to follow and his tests were really hard. His class wound up teaching me how to push through difficult times and make things work, if you do get his class, it will most certainly be a challenge, but use it as a chance to grow as a student.

Did well in this class thanks to youtube and studying with friends. The lectures are really fast and often not well explained, and the exam is very difficult! However, his powerpoint slides are very good, the "mobius" homework helps a lot and the tests are easy if you study hard. I enjoyed the course material but not the lectures. Pretty hardcore

Weren't allowed to ask questions in class. Quite accessible outside of class, however, it's not worth asking the question later. Not too hard, but also no clear directions for tests and exams. His current system of teaching online is not effective. Very hard to read and follow what he writes. Try to avoid.
I liked the professor. I appreciated the course notes being posted on brightspace, I was able to follow along at my own pace and I was able to catch up easily when I missed a class.

Honestly could not understand a single word he was saying in the lectures. Highlights everything on the page which makes it a headache to look at, and although we already know most of what he is teaching from high school, I left classes understanding math less than I did before. Avoid if possible
Does not upload lecturs online notes are not uploaded and messy poor teaching and mixes up words which makes lecturs hard to follow
This class was super great for a math class. He's super organized when it comes to picking questions that greatly reflect the course materials.

He's pretty average. His lectures are sort of hard to grasp at times -- especially more time-consuming topics like trig substitution and related rates. He stutters a LOT during lectures, but he posts valuable notes on Brightspace that are easy to follow. He's a really nice guy though, and is happy to help you outside class.
